  "body": "Type: Bug\r\n\r\nSummary: When user recovers an account, and changes his name in Profile settings - his old name is still displayed in chats (1-1 and a public chat) and on profile page\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nA new name should be displayed for a user each time it is updated\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\n\r\nAfter the account was recovered, an old name (the 'before-recovery' one) is still displays in chats and profile\r\n\r\n**Reproduction**\r\n\r\n1. Create a new account on device 1 for user A\r\n2. Add user A to 1-1 chat and a public chats he would share with user B\r\n3. Change the user's name from a default one for user A (ex. jkjkjkppp)\r\nCurrent result: At this point, username is updated in all the chats, and profile data for user A from perspective of user B\r\n4.  On device 2, recover your account for user A\r\n5. Change the username from a default to something new for user A (ex. jkjkjk111)\r\n6. Check all the chats and profile info for user A from the perspective of user B\r\n\r\nData of user A from a perspective of user B (username is jkjkjkppp):\r\n\r\n<img width=\"967\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/47095024-07289580-d235-11e8-8e86-87d9464075c5.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"963\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/47095011-fbd56a00-d234-11e8-9620-3149904d59bf.png\">\r\n\r\nScreen of user A (username is jkjkjk111):\r\n\r\n<img width=\"433\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/47094953-e102f580-d234-11e8-9d37-14f476fc7174.png\">\r\n\r\nNote: If you add a new person to contacts after step 5, this new contact can see your updated username. \r\nThis issue is valid only for your old contacts.\r\n\r\n**Additional Information**\r\n\r\nStatus version: Release 0.9.30 (10755) - a nightly from 17 Oct 2018\r\nTested on mobile and desktop:\r\niOS 12.0.1 \r\nAndroid 7.0 \r\nMacOS 10.13.4",
